      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (3.2M, 8.1M, 18.4M cells). Grid Convergence Index (GCI) on relative hemolysis index: 2.1% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Medium mesh (8.1M cells) selected for production runs, exceeding MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented and reproducible; boundary conditions must be traceable to published experimental protocols.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump experimental conditions sourced from Hariharan et al. (2011) and the FDA benchmark dataset. Flow rates (2.5–7.0 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM) fully documented. Boundary conditions applied in CFD model are directly traceable to published experimental protocols."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined; predicted QoI within 15% of experimental values for majority of operating points.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) computed for all 5 operating points. Mean absolute percentage error 8.3%; maximum error 13.7% at highest flow-speed combination. All predictions satisfy RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Quantitative agreement meets MRL 2 output comparison requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI used in validation must be directly relevant to the clinical decision; hemolysis index must be the primary output metric.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary QoI and directly maps to the clinical decision criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Shear stress exposure history along Lagrangian particle trajectories computed using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model, which is the standard approach for CFD hemolysis prediction in CPB applications."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation domain must overlap substantially with COU operating envelope; same pump geometry class and similar flow regime required.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which is geometrically representative of the CPB device class under assessment. Operating conditions in validation (2.5–7.0 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) span the COU operating envelope. Reynolds number regime consistent between validation and COU application."
    },
    {
